PART 2: DETAILED EXPLANATIONS

1. WHAT IS NOSQL?
Simple Definition
NoSQL = Not Only SQL
       = Databases that don't use traditional table structure
       = Alternative to relational databases
Full Explanation
Traditional SQL Database (Relational):
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│ USERS TABLE                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│ ID  │ Name    │ Email               │
├─────┼─────────┼─────────────────────┤
│ 1   │ Alice   │ alice@test.com      │
│ 2   │ Bob     │ bob@test.com        │
│ 3   │ Charlie │ charlie@test.com    │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘

Fixed columns, rows, structured

╔═════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║               NoSQL Database                        ║
╠═════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║ Collection: users                                   ║
║                                                     ║
║ Document 1:                                         ║
║ {                                                   ║
║   "_id": 1,                                         ║
║   "name": "Alice",                                  ║
║   "email": "alice@test.com",                        ║
║   "age": 25,                    ← Extra field      ║
║   "phone": "+1234567890"        ← Extra field      ║
║ }                                                   ║
║                                                     ║
