19. DISADVANTAGES OF NOSQL
❌ No Joins
Problem: Data in multiple documents

Users Collection:
{ _id: 1, name: "Alice" }

Posts Collection:
{ _id: 101, user_id: 1, title: "Hello" }

To get user with posts:
Must fetch user first
Then fetch all posts for that user
Combine manually

Solution: Embed data
{ _id: 1, name: "Alice", posts: [...] }

But: Creates duplication
If user_id changes, must update everywhere

❌ Data Duplication
Problem: Same data in multiple places

Users:
{ _id: 1, name: "Alice", email: "alice@test.com" }

Posts:
{ _id: 101, userName: "Alice", userEmail: "alice@test.com", title: "Hello" }

Alice updates email to "alice2@test.com"
Need to update in BOTH places
If forgot one place: inconsistency ❌

❌ Weaker Consistency
Problem: Eventual consistency

Alice updates profile
Bob reads immediately
Bob might see old data ⚠️

Takes few ms to sync across servers
Unpredictable timing
Can't rely on immediate consistency

