26. MONITORING & OPTIMIZATION
Key Metrics to Monitor
1. QUERY PERFORMANCE
   ├─ Slow queries (> 100ms)
   ├─ Query count per second
   ├─ Cache hit rate
   └─ Index usage

2. RESOURCE USAGE
   ├─ CPU usage
   ├─ Memory usage
   ├─ Disk I/O
   └─ Network bandwidth

3. DATA HEALTH
   ├─ Document count
   ├─ Data size
   ├─ Replication lag
   └─ Backup status

4. OPERATIONS
   ├─ Error rate
   ├─ Response time
   ├─ Throughput
   └─ Availability

Optimization Tips
1. ADD INDEXES
   - Identify slow queries
   - Create index on filter fields
   - Monitor index size

2. LIMIT DOCUMENT SIZE
   - MongoDB: < 16MB per document
   - Split into multiple documents if needed

3. USE PROJECTION
   - Only select needed fields
   - db.users.find({}, {name: 1, email: 1})

4. BATCH OPERATIONS
   - insertMany() instead of insertOne() loop
   - updateMany() instead of updateOne() loop

5. DENORMALIZE WISELY
   - Balance between embedding and referencing
   - Duplicate read-heavy data

6. CACHE FREQUENTLY ACCESSED DATA
   - Use Redis for caching
   - Set appropriate TTL

7. SHARD LARGE COLLECTIONS
   - Split data across servers
   - Choose good shard key

